OL,3,CHow much will Starmer's welfare u-turn
OL,4,Ccost him?
OL,6,FPerhaps in order to keep backbenchers
OL,7,Fonside with his welfare reforms, the
OL,8,Fprime minister has strongly hinted
OL,9,Fthat he agrees with them that the two
OL,10,Fchild benefit cap should be scrapped.
OL,12,FBut having forced the PM to partly
OL,13,Fabandon his welfare reforms they may
OL,14,Fbe unlikely to let him off the hook on
OL,15,Fthe two child cap.
OL,17,FScrapping is estimated to be worth
OL,18,Fanother #3.5bn.
